An Ogun East senatorial aspirant, Dr. Deji Ashiru, has wrapped up his consultation visits to nine councils in the district. Ward chairmen, principal officers, youth leaders, women leaders of councils Excos and Wards Excos in Ijebu East and Waterside local governments trooped out to welcome Ashiru. The constituents believe Ashiru can deliver the zones to All Progressives Congress (APC) in the elections.   ‘Political will needed to tackle insecurity’     ‘MC Oluomo didn’t sack secretariat workers’     APC to Igbo: identify with Lagos progress   One of the leaders on Ashiru’s entourage, APC Party Chairman in Ijebu Ode Kunle Aromolate said: “Ashiru is our good son and ambassador from Ijebu-Ode and we all came here in solidarity with him for his aspiration.   “He needs the support of all. I promise that he shall represent us well. We all followed him from Ijebu-Ode because Ashiru is purpose-driven.” Ashiru promised to give quality representation at the Senate to complement the agenda of the Dapo Abiodun Administration. Chairman of Ijebu East Wale Adedayo hailed Ashiru’s courage, and prayed for him to succeed.